{"word":"H1820 - דָּמָה - dâmâh - daw-mam' - Cease","slug":"H1820","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">דָּמָה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>dâmâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>daw-mam'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Cease"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D3;&#x05BC;&#x05DE;&#x05D4; - da&#x0302;ma&#x0302;h</b> - <i>daw-maw'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>be dumb</i> or <i>silent</i>; hence to <i>fail</i> or <i>perish</i>; transitively to <i>destroy: - </i>cease, be cut down (off), destroy, be brought to silence, be undone, X utterly."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1824\">H1824</a>"}]}